citations:
    citation-acok-arya-vii:
        source: source-acok
        properties:
            locator: "Arya VII"
            text_from_source: "She wondered how much longer she would have to include Weese in her prayer, and drifted off to sleep dreaming that on the morrow, when she woke, he'd be dead."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Arya names Weese as Jaqen's first target (dies when his dog tears out his throat). The chapter establishes Arya's nightly list of names as prayer. Lord Tywin departs Harrenhal."
